    "created_at": "2016-11-22T14:02:29Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-11-22T14:02:29Z",
    "body": "Since the issues you linked are referring to a bug in Chromium source base that Electron cannot workaround, I tested my issue against the latest Chromium build.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately the touch keyboard works as expected (for my use case) both in Google Chrome and Chromium, but not in Electron: it appears when I touch a text field and disappears when I click elsewhere, while in Electron it tries to appear but it fails.\r\n\r\nI've reported the same issue to the [electron-windows-store](https://github.com/felixrieseberg/electron-windows-store) project since I wrapped packaged Electron in a Windows Store app that could potentially interfere."
  },
